<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6075> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6075" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proquaestor, when with Lentulus Spinther and others he attacked the fleet of Dolabella off the coast of southern Asia Minor and northern Syria (Cic. Fam. 12.15.2, and 13.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10478> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10478" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. Caes. 67.4-5, App. BC 2.119. Joined the Liberators on the Capitol on the Ides of March. Unlike C. Octavius and Lentulus Spinther, he is not explicitly mentioned as having claimed to have been an assassin, but might have been a senator nonetheless." .
